# TriageLLM environment variables (example)
#
# Copy this file to ".env" and uncomment/edit the lines you want to override.
#   cp .env.example .env      (macOS/Linux)
#   Copy-Item .env.example .env   (PowerShell)
#
# ".env" is git-ignored so your real values never get committed. TriageLLM does
# NOT auto-load ".env" itself -- these are documentation of the variables the
# proxy and CLIs read from the process environment. Set them in your shell, your
# launcher, or via a tool like direnv/dotenv before starting the proxy.
#
# Every value below shows its DEFAULT. You only need to set a variable to change
# it from that default.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ollama connection
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Where the Ollama daemon lives. Default is loopback. A non-localhost value is
# REFUSED unless ALLOW_REMOTE_OLLAMA=1 (M-6 SSRF guard) -- remote Ollama is
# opt-in, off by default.
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434

# Set to 1 to allow a non-localhost OLLAMA_BASE_URL. Leave unset for the safe
# default (localhost only).
# ALLOW_REMOTE_OLLAMA=0

# Read by the OLLAMA DAEMON (not by TriageLLM) -- points Ollama at your model
# store. On this project the models live on an SSD at D:\Ollama\Models. Set this
# as a system/user env var and restart the Ollama daemon so it inherits it.
# OLLAMA_MODELS=D:\Ollama\Models

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Startup behaviour
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Skip the critic warmup call at module import. Set to 1 for pytest / health.py /
# uat.py and any script that imports router_hook without a running event loop.
# conftest.py sets this automatically during test collection; health.bat /
# uat.bat set it too. Only set it by hand when running router_hook scripts
# directly.
# TRIAGELLM_SKIP_WARMUP=0

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ollama fast-fail circuit breaker (DEF-004)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Master switch for the fast-fail circuit breaker. When on (default), an
# unreachable Ollama fails a request in ~2s instead of ~32s and keeps the proxy
# alive. Set to 0 to disable.
# TRIAGELLM_OLLAMA_FAST_FAIL_ENABLED=1

# Connect timeout for the preflight /api/tags probe.
# TRIAGELLM_OLLAMA_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=2.0

# How long the circuit stays OPEN (fail-instantly) after a failure before a
# HALF_OPEN re-probe is allowed.
# TRIAGELLM_OLLAMA_CIRCUIT_COOLDOWN_SECONDS=10.0

# Read/write timeout for the preflight probe.
# TRIAGELLM_OLLAMA_PROBE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=2.0

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Capability Routing v0.2 (shadow mode)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Enable capability-routing shadow recording. Default OFF -- when unset the
# capability sidecar is bypassed entirely (no behaviour change, no ledger
# columns written). Set to 1 to record what a capability-aware router WOULD have
# chosen (it never changes actual routing in v0.2).
# TRIAGELLM_CAPABILITY_ROUTING_ENABLED=0

# Comma-separated list of capability packs to activate, overriding the
# config.yaml route_llm.capability_routing.packs list. Example: coder,writing
# TRIAGELLM_CAPABILITY_PACKS=coder

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloud escalation (optional, last-resort)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Cloud escalation is OFF by default in config.yaml. When enabled there, the
# proxy reads the API key by ENV-VAR NAME (config: api_key_env, default
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY) -- the key value is NEVER stored in YAML. If the named var
# is unset at request time, cloud escalation is silently skipped and the handoff
# message is returned instead. Set whichever provider key your config.yaml's
# api_key_env points at:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
